													Diagnostic and antibody testing for COVID-19 is increasing significantly as governments and health authorities look for data to inform decisions about how to safely end lockdowns and restart economies. While public health and safety concerns are paramount, there are numerous privacy questions worth asking when testing and health monitoring for COVID-19. IAPP Legal Research Fellow Cathy Cosgrove explores some of those issues and questions in this piece for The Privacy Advisor.Full Story
Infograp...
